<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
  <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink207-kilavi"> maḻaiyiṉmaiyāṟ ṟiṉai yuṇaṅkum vil̤aiyamāṭṭā puṉaṅkāppac ceṉ ṟavarai yetirppaṭalāmeṉ ṟeṇṇiyirunta vitu kūṭātāyiṟ ṟeṉa veṟuttirunta talaimakaṭkut toḻi colliyatu. </p>
      <p xml:lang="en"> What the confidante told the heroine, who sat in dismay that [her plan of] intending to meet him, having gone to protect the field [under the pretext that] ‘the millet will dry up without rain” and that “they will not mature,” had become impossible.   </p>
      </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink207">
<l>aṉṉāy vāḻivēṇ ṭaṉṉai naṉṟu</l>
<l>muṇaṅkala kollō niṉ ṟiṉaiyē yuvakkā</l>
<l>ṇiṇampoti vaḻukkiṟ ṟōṉṟu</l>
<l>maḻaitalai vaittavar maṇineṭuṅ kuṉṟē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l> Oh Mother, please Mother, </l>

<l rend="space">look there, </l>
<l>won’t your millet truly dry up?  </l>
<l rend="space indent">His sapphire, tall mountain</l>
<l rend="indent">with clouds placed upon [its] peak,</l>
<l rend="indent">appears like suet encased in flesh. </l>

      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
